Text.Value: I'm not giving out any more free copies. I'll be putting the bog-paper shop out of business.
Oh look, today's star. Everyone else might think the sun shines out your hole, but I don't care. Gazette's [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54] gold, same as always.
Let me see that Gazette. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
You're the boss, boss.
I'm not interested.
You know what'd really annoy the writers? Giving me a free copy.
What is the paper called?
So you're still standing here why?
I'll take a copy. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
There you go, hero. Don't let the fame go to your head - if it gets any fatter, it'll explode.
Get your copy of the Baldur's Mouth Gazette here. 'News that bites b-' Oh. You again. It's [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54] gold, same as before.

EditorData.NodeContext: said in a montone, humdrum way

Text.Value: Ah, the Baldur's Mouth Gazette?
No, thank you.
Do I look like a library to you? Get your free reads somewhere else, cheap prick.
My stupid dad makes me sell these shite-rags. Pillock. If you want one, it's [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54] gold.
Paper says a lot of bad things about you - I'll add 'cheap bastard' to the list. Take one. What do I care?
You're selling newspapers?
Yeah - the best one in town. Also the only one in town. Want a copy? [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54] gold.
Honestly, if you pissed them writers off, you're good in my books. Either way, it's gold for a copy, if you're curious. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
I'll take a copy. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
You want a copy of this rag? [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54] gold - make it quick.
What's with the attitude?
I don't want one.
Ooh, bad luck. You're plastered all over today's gazette, and it ain't pleasant reading.
Neither am I, dickhole.
'The Baldur's Mouth Gazette. When the Mouth barks, the Fist bites...' Uh... I forget the real slogan, but you get the idea. Now, buy a copy or leave.
Works great as toilet paper if you run out.

Synopsis: Dialog with a paper seller on the road between the docks and the Upper City Gate
